00000>(6/21/01 6:12:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Newbies and mains</span><hr size=1> Ok, I play a lot of characters. I'll make one, twink em, get em to 20 and delete em at the drop of a hat. Got two accounts full.<br>
<br>
Anyways, some I solo thru the teens and some group. With my newest warrior I've been grouping pretty much exclusivly since lvl 5 or so.  <br>
<br>
I've noticed that in places like Oasis, where you are fighting a lot of reds, that teamwork is crucial. But not near as crucial as knowing your role.  I've seen clerics pulling.  Hardly anyone medding, but saying "GTG 40%" and stuff.  Seen people training specs to the dock (like anyone there can help them).  I've seen deaths because druid was oom and instead of medding for heal, thinks he can melee. (heres a hint, hitting for 3-8 points of damage isn't gonna help, let the tanks hit)<br>
<br>
BUT all this is sorta excusable. Everyone is getting to know thier new class. You can tell too.  The tanks who play cleric mostly, they will be real patient with pulls, ask about mana. THEY will call med break, and will normally do it right.<br>
<br>
Then the caster who plays a tank main.  He will never be full mana, will never ever med thru any fight, even if it means draining every last drop of mana.  Will open with a nuke.<br>
<br>
The newbie enchanter.  Will try his hardest to mez, but everyone will break it.  Will try his darnedest to color stun, but will be too far away.  Will die a lot.  Oh and will waste mana on enfeeblement and weakness.<br>
<br>
The cleric who plays a melee main.  Will never buff, will pull. Will usually be lom. And will nuke heavy.  Hasn't quite realized that we aren't fighting "A giant rats" any more.<br>
<br>
The newbie monk. Will never stop pulling, will totally disregard the status of the group and will usually be with a group of people only once, until he gets on the shitlist (yes, we keep one)<br>
<br>
Then there are pallys. Half tank, half loot hog. (sorry had a bad expeience in oasis this week)<br>
<br>
The shaman. Have yet to run into a bad lowbie yet, all seem to know thier role. That is until they try and melee and get squashed. Shaman should med and stay away from monster when in group. <br>
<br>
I'm not insinuating I know what I am doing either. I fall under category of Warrior with cleric/enchanter mains. So I pull very slow, make sure everyone has plenty of mana, and I get bitched at a lot.   Oh I'll break mez in a heartbeat, and ironically I have a 52 enchanter as well, would think I'd be better at it.  I do fight to the death, so thats one good thing.<br>
<br>
Guess I'm lucky, group with same people about every day, with 2 "wildcard" slots, prolly helps.<br>
