<br>
Nothing like when I very first started playing, asked a level 9 shaman in group for a sow, and he tried to charge me 2 plats for it. Talk about tacky.<br>
<br>
The worst is when someone in group tries to sell you something you need he looted from a mob you all killed. Greater Lightstones come to mind.<br>
<br>
My warrior is getting very near Lake of Ill Omen level. going to try my best to stay away from that mess. I think everyone goes straight from Oasis to LoIO. By far, worse grouping expeiences have been in has been in Ill Omen, and most involved an iksar monk who pulled too fast. Do they solo too much or something?  And druids should stay on the zone walls medding alone until they realize they usually don't have to nuke something when its running away with 20 hp left. And a dot at 10% health isn't worth it. :)<br>
<br>
But as far as newbie groups go, once get in one with several experienced and professional twinks, you can do about anything.<br>
<br>
